<title type="html"><![CDATA[‘Abd al-‘Azīz Ar-Rājihī on Political Demonstrations]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1286&amp;p=1367#p1367"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">‘Abd al-‘Azīz Ar-Rājihī on Political Demonstrations</span></strong><br /><br />Original Title: الفتاوى الشرعية في القضايا العصرية<br /><br />‘Abd al-‘Azīz Ar-Rājihī[1] on Political Demonstrations[2]<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Question:</span></strong> What is your opinion of those who say political demonstrations are allowable in order to pressure the leaders or governments?<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Answer:</span></strong> These demonstrations are not from the actions of Muslims. They are foreign (to Islam) and were never known except by way of the western countries of disbelief.[3]<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Footnotes:</span></strong><br /><br />[1] ‘Abd al-‘Azīz Ar-Rājihī: One of the leading scholars and instructors of Saudi Arabia today.<br /><br />[2] This fatwā was taken from a book called “al-Fatāwā al-Shar’iyyah fī al-Qadhāyā Al-‘Asriyyah,” a<br />collection of various rulings by Muhammad Ibn Fahd al-Ḥusayn.<br /><br />[3] Taken from the magazine: Safīnah al-Najāḥ (no. 2, Janurary 1997).<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.authentic-translations.com/">http://www.authentic-translations.com/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Wed Mar 22, 2017 12:14 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
